{
  "doc_id": "36323",
  "text": "FR-α is a glycosyl phosphatidylinositol-anchored glycoprotein that is found on the surface of many epithelial cells (Elnakat & Ratnam, 2004; [CITATION_1] . It binds folate at high affinity and mediates its transmembrane transport into the cell cytoplasm for use in purine, pyrimidine and ultimately DNA biosynthesis, a process that is essential for rapidly dividing tumour cells (Antony, 1996; [CITATION_2] . FR- is overexpressed in 72% of MM, regardless of subtypes. Furthermore, the level of expression is 2-4-fold higher in the tumour, compared with normal tissues [CITATION_3] . It has also been shown to be a T cell target [CITATION_4] . While the targeting potential of this antigen has been realised in many studies [CITATION_5] , it has not been tested in MM.",
